.TH pohoda-sharepoint-link-fixer 1 "" "version 1.8.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pohoda-sharepoint-link-fixer \- attach missing and repair wrong SharePoint PDF links on Pohoda bank records
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pohoda-sharepoint-link-fixer
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Validates and repairs the SharePoint statement PDF links on Pohoda bank records for a given period.
Use when bank records were imported without the SharePoint URL attachment, or when an earlier un-scoped import cross-attached statements between the several bank accounts of one Pohoda company (so a record for one account links to another account's statement).
.PP
By default the tool runs in \fBdry-run\fR mode (LINK_FIX_APPLY=false): it reports what it would change without writing anything. Set LINK_FIX_APPLY=true to apply.
.PP
The tool performs three stages:
.IP "1." 4
Connect to SharePoint and list PDF statement files for the configured period, filtered by ACCOUNT_NUMBER embedded in the filename.
.IP "2." 4
Query Pohoda MSSQL for bank records (BV table) in the period together with their current URL attachment. When POHODA_BANK_IDS is set, only records belonging to that bank account (matched via sUcet.IDS) are considered.
.IP "3." 4
For each record: attach the statement link when missing; when the existing link points to another account's statement, repoint it to the correct PDF (or remove it when no correct PDF exists); leave already-correct links untouched. Write a JSON report.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output=FILE
Write JSON report to FILE instead of RESULT_FILE env var (default: php://stdout).
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-environment=FILE
Path to .env configuration file (default: ../.env).
.SH REPORT FORMAT
The JSON report written to RESULT_FILE contains:
.IP \(bu 4
.B account
\- the configured ACCOUNT_NUMBER
.IP \(bu 4
.B bank_ids
\- value of POHODA_BANK_IDS (null when unset)
.IP \(bu 4
.B since, until
\- resolved date range
.IP \(bu 4
.B sharepoint_files
\- list of statement dates found in SharePoint for the period
.IP \(bu 4
.B apply
\- true when changes were written, false for a dry-run
.IP \(bu 4
.B bank_records_checked
\- number of BV records inspected in the period
.IP \(bu 4
.B ok
\- count of records whose link was already correct (left untouched)
.IP \(bu 4
.B fixed
\- array of records that had a missing link now attached (pohodaId, cislo, date, filename, url)
.IP \(bu 4
.B corrected
\- array of wrong-account links repointed to the correct PDF (pohodaId, docId, date, from, to, url)
.IP \(bu 4
.B removed
\- array of wrong-account links deleted because no correct PDF exists (pohodaId, docId, date, was)
.IP \(bu 4
.B skipped
\- records with a missing link for which no matching SharePoint file was found
.IP \(bu 4
.B errors
\- error messages for failed attachment/repair attempts
.IP \(bu 4
.B exitcode
\- final exit code
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
SharePoint listing failed.
.TP
.B 2
MSSQL query failed.
.TP
.B 3
One or more link attach/correct/remove operations failed.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ACCOUNT_NUMBER
Bank account number. Used to filter SharePoint files by matching the account number embedded in the PDF filename.
.TP
.B POHODA_BANK_IDS
Pohoda bank account abbreviation (sUcet.IDS, e.g.\& RB). When set, only BV records belonging to this bank account are processed. When unset, all bank records are considered.
.TP
.B IMPORT_SCOPE
Time scope of records to fix (e.g.\& last_month, this_month, yesterday, 2024-01-01>2024-01-31). Default: last_month. Overridden by DATE_FROM/DATE_TO when explicitly set.
.TP
.B DATE_FROM
Explicit start date for the period (YYYY-MM-DD or PHP date expression). Overrides IMPORT_SCOPE when set.
.TP
.B DATE_TO
Explicit end date for the period (YYYY-MM-DD or PHP date expression). Overrides IMPORT_SCOPE when set.
.TP
.B LINK_FIX_APPLY
When true, apply changes to Pohoda (attach/correct/remove links). When false or unset (default), run in dry-run mode: report intended changes without writing anything. Run a dry-run first and review the report before applying.
.TP
.B DB_CONNECTION, DB_HOST, DB_PORT, DB_DATABASE, DB_USERNAME, DB_PASSWORD
SQL Server connection parameters for accessing the Pohoda database.
.TP
.B DB_SETTINGS
Additional DSN settings (e.g.\& ;TrustServerCertificate=true).
.TP
.B OFFICE365_TENANT, OFFICE365_SITE, OFFICE365_PATH
SharePoint location to list statement PDFs from.
.TP
.B OFFICE365_CLIENTID, OFFICE365_CLSECRET
Application credentials for SharePoint (used when OFFICE365_USERNAME/PASSWORD are not set).
.TP
.B OFFICE365_USERNAME, OFFICE365_PASSWORD
User credentials for SharePoint.
.TP
.B RESULT_FILE
Output path for the JSON report (default: php://stdout).
.TP
.B APP_DEBUG
Set to true to enable verbose debug logging.
.TP
.B EASE_LOGGER
Log output target (default: console|syslog).
.SH AUTHOR
